1. Expose fewer than five public methods
1. Keep classes under 250 lines of code
1. Don't use static methods
1. Thinks about the "is a" relationship when creating objects - don't create procedures

If you want to know the answer to the question "Why? ", then feel free to buy the books from Yegor on [amazon](https://www.amazon.com/-/de/dp/1534908307/ref=sr_1_1?__mk_de_DE=%C3%85M%C3%85%C5%BD%C3%95%C3%91&keywords=Yegor+Bugayenko&qid=1654181466&sr=8-1).
